headline: Disney Has Another Huge Hit at the Box Office. Is It Finally Time to Buy?
summary: Walt Disney released a strong second-quarter report last month.  Walt Disney (NYSE: DIS) might be the top name in entertainment, but that doesn't automatically mean its stock is always in good shape.  The company reported solid results for the 2025 fiscal second quarter (ended March 29), and its newest film release, the live-action Lilo and Stitch, had a fantastic opening weekend.
